sidebar.tutorialSidebar.category.Menu.li.message: Displayed menus and access to them are limited to user access level. Menus displayed in the system might not be available in all trucks. Slide up and down the menu screens to navigate the menus. Press on a menu item to enter that item. Press the arrow at the top left to go back a page. If you hold it for more than 1.5 s, you will return to the home screen.

sidebar.tutorialSidebar.category.Monitor.description: The label for category Monitor in sidebar tutorialSidebar

sidebar.tutorialSidebar.category.Monitor.message: Service Menu will enable you to reset service hours from the truck.  Three different options might be available depending on which one his closest to happen: First Service, Standard Service and Full Service. After pressing Reset you will be asked to confirm that action.  If so, the service hourmeters will be restart counting a new period. If logged on user is higher than level 4, Interlock Management option will also be available.

Pedestrian CAN tiller head or standard configurable inputs and pedestrian hydraulic valve block Type 2 â€“ For AMEOP trucks. Standard configurable input and AMEOP valveblock. Type 3 â€“ For CS3000 trucks. Pedestrian CAN tiller head or standard configurable inputs and AMEOP valveblock Type 4 â€“ For SPT trucks. SPT special hydraulics. CAN joystick and custom valves Type 5 â€“ For SPT trucks. SPT special hydraulics. CAN joystick and custom valves Type 6 â€“ For CBE70, CUBE, MR4 and M-ESL trucks. CAN joystick with â€˜Type 0â€™ configurable output valves. Type 7 â€“ For CBE4000_SHAPE trucks.
